      • getChordType

        public static ChordTypesEnum getChordType(int[] chord)
                                   throws java.lang.Exception
        Obtain the corresponding enum chord type given a 12-interval integer array.
        Parameters:
        chord - A 12-interval integer array which corresponds to the twelve main musical tones. The chord type will be computed based on the distance between the indices of values in the array that are > 0. For example, a C-major chord can be represented as [10, 0, 0, 0, 20, 0, 0, 64, 0, 0, 0, 0].
        Returns:
        The corresponding chord type if this is indeed a known chord of size 3 or more. Otherwise, this method will return null if it does not know the given chord type. For example a chord array with only 2 notes in it will make this function return a null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Thrown if the chord integer array is invalid.
